Ah, I see what you mean about the flickering. It worked for me because I was using 8x8 sprites, but with 8x16, it needs to be a little different.<br /><br />I just played around with the constants a bit, try subtracting $14 from currindex, and adding $54 to offset, and see if that helps at all.<br /><br />Really, as long as the value you subtract from currindex ends in either x4 or xC, (similar for the value you add to offset) you can play around with these numbers and see if there's one that looks best for your game.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=21">Drag</a> — Sun Jan 04, 2015 3:11 am</p><hr />
